<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-26T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-26T21:00:00-05:00" n="61" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d61">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/612a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Afghanistan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Thayer</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-26T22:00:00-04:00">June 26,
                                    1942—10 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>6. The Department fully approves of New Delhi’s suggestion that you
                            express to the Afghan Government the regret of this Government that an
                            American army plane inadvertently flew over Afghan territory.</p>
                        <p>Please keep the Department fully informed of developments.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>